SEATTLE (AP) — SEATTLE (AP) — BSquare Corp. (BSQR) on Tuesday reported a loss of $1.2 million in its fourth quarter.On a per-share basis, the Seattle-based company said it had a loss of 6 cents. Losses, adjusted for restructuring costs, came to 5 cents per share.The software and engineering services provider posted revenue of $8 million in the period.For the year, the company reported that its loss widened to $3.9 million, or 19 cents per share. Revenue was reported as $36.5 million.In the final minutes of trading on Tuesday, the company’s shares hit $1.25. A year ago, they were trading at $1.50._____This story was generated by  Automated Insights  (http://automatedinsights.com/ap) using data from Zacks Investment Research. Access a  Zacks stock report on BSQR  at https://www.zacks.com/ap/BSQR